/* Ancient history */  Included the Phoenicians invention of the alphabet under 'Ancient history' as it should be mentioned here too, and not just under articles (alphabet) and (Phoenicians).

Removed French from the languages. Being able to say "Hi" and "Thank you" in French doesn't qualify as speaking 'some' French. Shakira was recently in Morocco & told the people she didn't know French and that's why she brought a translator with her.

/* Religion */  Added that the percentages are only those of the MAJOR religions in Lebanon but there are OTHER religions & nonbelievers too. Removed bar graph since it's already in pie chart and it doesn't represent ALL the religions of Lebanon.
Undid revision 513228835 by [[Special:Contributions/178.128.44.232|178.128.44.232]] ([[User talk:178.128.44.232|talk]]) It is a reliable source and a known fact. Reporting vandalism.
Removed uncited information with cited information. The Bouzouki was not of Greek origin and was brought to Greece from Asia Minor, a popular known fact.

I don't know who put 3000BC, but there is no exact dated history of when the Phoenicians started their civilization, but they found objects that dates back roughly to 8000BC when they used to be called the Canaanites.

Removed misleading information which was speculation. Arabic music gets most of its influence from Ancient Middle East, not Ancient Greece. Greece was influenced by Ancient  Egyptian & Ancient Middle East itself.

Belly Dance was and is not a Greek dance. Never was it's origin from Greece. The world knows it's always been from Mesopotamia, Middle East. Greeks need to stop spamming this article with false sources.

/* Religion */  CIA had errors w/ simple math. 27 + 27 = 54 not 59. Also the CIA is not a legit source anyway, there were many errors that were not included in this article for that very reason. Nobody uses the term Irreligion. That's why Other is used.
Re-added what was was initially in this article, her name in Arabic font. Her name, Salma, as well as Hayek are both of Arabic origin, and are not Spanish names.
/* Early life */  corrected her father's info. He is of Lebanese descent,  born in Lebanon. He moved to Mexico as an adult to start a business. His last name is Hayek, corrected that too.
/* Religion */  Grouped other religions with non religions since there is no point of having two in the graph and the % is not accurately known as to who is atheist or agnostic.

/* Religion */ corrected the 56 to 54 since 27 plus 27 is 54 and Druze do not consider themselves muslim. Also these percentages alone are not accurate. There are a lot more who have "Other" as a religion than is beign stated here.
This was initially in the article but some had removed it. The name Shakira is of Arabic origin, not Spanish.

Minor editing - added that Lebanon is a Levantine country since that should be pointed out. I also removed Armenian language as a national language since it is not, Armenians only make up 1% of the population. English language is spoken more commonly.
